===Etymology===
From earlier {{m|en|twise}}, from {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|twies}}, {{m|enm|twiȝes}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|twīġes||twice}}, from {{m|ang|twīwa}}, {{m|ang|twīġa}} {{gloss|"twice"; whence Middle English {{m|enm|twie||twice}}}} + {{m|ang|-es|pos=adverbial genitive ending}}. Related to Saterland Frisian {{m|stq|twäie||twice}}, Middle Low German {{m|gml|twiges}}, {{m|gml|twies||twice}}, Middle High German {{m|gmh|zwies||twies}}. Compare also [[twi-]] meaning two or both.

